      <h1>About This Directory</h1>

      <h2>What is Sydney Anxiety Psychology?</h2>
      <p>Sydney Anxiety Psychology is an independent directory helping people in Sydney find AHPRA-registered telehealth psychologists who specialise in anxiety. It is not a clinic, a practice, or a therapy service. This directory helps people identify suitable practitioners; we do not provide clinical care.</p>

      <h2>Why we built it</h2>
      <p>Finding a telehealth psychologist for anxiety is harder than it should be. Most directories are generic, most practice websites obscure their fees, and the Medicare system is genuinely confusing. The combination of these barriers ("who do I contact?", "what will it cost?", "does telehealth even work?") is enough to stop many people from getting support they need and are already looking for.</p>
      <p>This directory exists to remove those barriers: clear fees, accurate information about telehealth, and a straightforward way to connect with a suitable practitioner.</p>

      <h2>How practitioner profiles work</h2>
      <p>This directory uses a public-register model. Here is how it works:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Profiles are built from the AHPRA public register.</strong> The <a href="https://www.ahpra.gov.au/Registration/Registers-of-Practitioners.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AHPRA Registers of Practitioners</a> is freely and publicly accessible government data. Skeleton profiles contain only: the practitioner's full name, registration type (as confirmed by AHPRA), and principal practice suburb. No contact details, no clinical claims, no fabricated information.</li>
        <li><strong>Profiles are marked unclaimed until the practitioner engages.</strong> Every pre-built profile is clearly labelled "Unclaimed" and includes a prominent link for the practitioner to claim their profile or request removal. Unclaimed profiles contain no booking links or contact information.</li>
        <li><strong>Listing is free. There is no referral fee.</strong> We do not charge practitioners to list, and we do not take a commission or referral fee when a patient enquiry is passed to a practitioner. This may change in future; any change would be communicated to listed practitioners with clear notice and consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Practitioners can request removal at any time.</strong> We process removal requests within 24 hours, no questions asked. See the <a href="/listing-removal/">listing removal page</a> for instructions.</li>
        <li><strong>All listings are AHPRA-verified.</strong> All practitioners listed hold current AHPRA registration, which you can independently verify at <a href="https://www.ahpra.gov.au/Registration/Registers-of-Practitioners.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ahpra.gov.au</a>. We use the registration type confirmed by AHPRA (registered psychologist or endorsed clinical psychologist) and do not upgrade or downgrade titles.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to report inaccurate information</h2>
      <p>If you notice information on this directory that appears to be inaccurate, including practitioner credentials, registration type, or suburb, please contact us. Accuracy is a core commitment of this directory. Practitioners can also request removal at any time via the <a href="/listing-removal/">listing removal page</a>.</p>

      <h2>What this directory is not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We are not a clinical service and cannot provide psychological advice</li>
        <li>We are not a crisis service. For urgent mental health support, contact Lifeline on 13 11 14 or Beyond Blue on 1300 22 4636.</li>
        <li>We do not guarantee specific outcomes from any practitioners listed</li>
        <li>We are not affiliated with Medicare, AHPRA, or any government body</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>We collect minimal personal information and handle it in accordance with the Australian Privacy Act 1988. Skeleton profiles contain only AHPRA public register data. No personal data beyond what practitioners explicitly submit via the claim form is stored. See our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for details.</p>

